      <body xml:id="relative-location">
         <head>relative location</head>
         <p>If the location of an ancient place which does not exist any more
    is known only in relation to another place, you can use
    <tag>location type='relative'</tag> and provide a
    description, for example "5 days walk from Gondar". You
    can encode with <gi>measure</gi> also the unit and
    quantity of the distance if you can and want to.</p>
         <p>example:</p>
         <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
<place type="port" sameAs="Q378940">
               <placeName>Adulis</placeName>
               <location type="relative" source="#FattovichMunro"><desc>20 stades from the actual port</desc></location>
            <listBibl type="secondary">
               <bibl xml:id="FattovichMunro">
                  <ptr target="bm:FattovichMunro2003EnAeAdulis"/>
               </bibl>
            </listBibl>
               <note></note>
            </place>
</egXML>
      </body>
   </text>
